FBIS4-60616 "drnes102_v_94001" FBIS-NES-94-102 Daily Report 14 May 1994 Pakistan Asif Ali Sees New Phase of Relationship With U.S. Asif Ali Sees New Phase of Relationship With U.S. BK1405150794 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 1400 GMT 14 May 94 BK1405150794 Islamabad PTV Television Network English BFN [Text] Foreign Minister Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali has said Pakistan and the United States are entering a new phase of their relationship. Inaugurating a seminar on Pakistan's Foreign Policy Achievements in Islamabad today, the foreign minister said Pakistan-U.S. relations were marred due to the unjust Pressler Amendment. Both Pakistan and the United States have recognized Pressler Amendment as a bad law. He said the United States is not attempting to roll back Pakistan's nuclear program on a unilateral basis. Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali said soon after the assumption of office, the prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, embarked upon a program to end Pakistan's diplomatic isolation. She undertook measures to restore Pakistan's image as a modern, democratic, and forward-looking state committed to promotion and protection of human rights and desirous of building tension-free relations with all countries, especially its neighbors.
